Set linked incident to closure playbook (#189)

Closes a linked XSOAR child incidents.

Child is determined by verifying if the parent incident ID field is populated. If there is no parent incident id then all linked incidents will be closed.

If there is a parent incident ID then no action is taken to prevent a child incident from closing other linked incidents.

Close Ticket and upload closure notes (#24)

Close a ticket on the CDC and ServiceNow platforms.

Values passed to the script take precedence over values defined in the incident. If there are no values  passed to the script or set in the incident then the default defined inside the script are used:

close_notes = "Closed by post-processing rule"
close_reason = "Investigation completed"

The values are not defined as defaults on the script settings arguments to ensure that argument and incident values are evaluated independently.

Closure playbook. Carries out the following actions before generating the report and closing the incident.

- Collects closure details if closure fields are not already set
 -Verifies that an incident owner is assigned 
- Verifies there are no open SITs
- Verifies that the affected user and incident owner are not the same
- Synchronises the XSOAR and ServiceNow priority and severity fields to ensure they are in-sync before closure.
- Closes tickets on ServiceNow and CDC platforms
